# Frozen regression fixture for Listeria innocua (taxon 1642).
#
# This directory intentionally EXISTS but contains NO proteome.fasta. It
# reproduces the exact failing state from bus brief #124: upstream Makefile
# stages create build/species/<id>/ for a newly-active species before the
# proteome-selection stage has produced proteome.fasta.
#
# Old check_for_proteome guarded on `species_path.exists()`, so with this dir
# present it skipped on-demand selection; check_for_skips then called
# .stat().st_size on the missing proteome.fasta and crashed the whole run with
# FileNotFoundError. See tests/test_species_1642.py.
